---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="LinkedIn Pack — Diego Cuñado">
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wide">Confidential · March 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-2 mb-4">LinkedIn Pack</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">Copy, paste, done. Todo listo para meter en LinkedIn.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-900/30 border border-blue-700/50 rounded-lg p-5 mb-10">
      <p class="text-blue-200 font-semibold mb-2">📋 Instrucciones</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Cada sección tiene el texto final listo para copiar. He fusionado lo práctico (mi review) con los marcos teóricos (la #215: Walker, Pearl, adversarial audit). Donde hay opciones, elige la que más te resuene. Todo en inglés para LinkedIn.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- HEADLINE -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">1. Headline</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">220 caracteres máx. Es lo primero que se ve, en búsquedas, comentarios, invitaciones, todo.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-2">OPCIÓN A — Narrativa de reinvención (recomendada)</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-gray-200 text-sm select-all">Head of Product @ Hire Space · AI Product Builder · Law &amp; Economics → Tech</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">La flecha cuenta tu historia en un carácter. Alto índice de ensamblaje (Walker) comprimido en formato escaneable. Te diferencia de los 10.000 "Head of Product" que hay en LinkedIn UK.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-yellow-400 font-semibold mb-2">OPCIÓN B — Orientada a búsqueda / SEO</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-gray-200 text-sm select-all">Head of Product · Marketplace &amp; Enterprise SaaS · AI Product Development · Bilingual EN/ES</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">Más keywords, más apariciones en búsquedas de recruiters. Menos personalidad. Útil si quieres maximizar volumen de inbound.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-purple-400 font-semibold mb-2">OPCIÓN C — Híbrida</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-gray-200 text-sm select-all">Head of Product @ Hire Space · Building AI products &amp; marketplace platforms · Law → Tech</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">Combina narrativa con keywords. Buen equilibrio.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ABOUT -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">2. About</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">2.600 caracteres máx. Estructura de la #215: Hook → Narrative → Proof → Signal. Tu README.md profesional.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-3">TEXTO FINAL — copia todo el bloque</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-5 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">I studied Law and Economics and ended up building AI products. That path wasn't planned, but in hindsight every step made the next one possible.

I'm Head of Product at Hire Space, the UK's largest venue marketplace (100K+ venues). I lead product strategy across the full platform: marketplace, venue profiles, search, booking, conversion, and the enterprise product (Hire Space 360). Working across engineering, design, and commercial teams to ship things that actually move metrics. Before that, I built products at ODICCI, JustPark, and The Ringley Group, always in the space between technology, users, and business models.

My background gives me a different lens. Law trained me to think in systems and edge cases. Economics trained me to think in incentives and trade-offs. Product management is where both come together: understanding what to build, why it matters, and what happens when real people use it.

I'm hands-on with technology. Not just "comfortable with data" comfortable: I build things. I've shipped an AI-powered food tracker (chowdown.me, 500+ monthly users), an AI landing page optimisation tool (darwin.page), and I work daily with LLMs, APIs, TypeScript, and Python. I believe the best product leaders understand the stack, not just the backlog.

What I do best: take complex, ambiguous problems and turn them into shipped solutions. Across marketplaces, enterprise SaaS, and AI-driven products.

Currently exploring opportunities where product thinking meets AI. Open to conversations.</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-3">~1,400 caracteres. Deja espacio de sobra. Si quieres añadir algo más específico (números de Hire Space, por ejemplo), cabe perfectamente.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- EXPERIENCE: HIRE SPACE -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">3. Experience — Hire Space</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Dos roles: Head of Product + Senior PM. Cada uno necesita su descripción.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-2">HEAD OF PRODUCT (Oct 2023 — Present)</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-5 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Leading product strategy for the UK's largest venue marketplace (100K+ venues, serving corporate clients and agencies).

· Own the product roadmap and lead a cross-functional team across engineering, design, and commercial
· Built and scaled Hire Space 360, the enterprise platform, from concept to active adoption by large corporates
· Drive product discovery, experimentation, and data-driven prioritisation across marketplace search, booking, and supplier tools
· Bridge commercial strategy with technical execution to ship faster with less waste
· Introduced structured frameworks for stakeholder alignment and product decision-making

Key focus areas: marketplace dynamics, enterprise SaaS, AI-assisted features, conversion optimisation.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-yellow-400 font-semibold mb-2">SENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER (anterior)</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-5 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Managed the core marketplace product: search, venue profiles, booking flow, and supplier-facing tools.

· Led product discovery for key revenue-driving features
· Worked closely with engineering to improve platform performance and reliability
· Owned stakeholder management across sales, operations, and customer success
· Built the foundation that evolved into the enterprise product (Hire Space 360)</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-3">⚠️ Necesito que ajustes los detalles si no son exactos. Y si tienes números (revenue growth, conversión, adoption rates), mételos. Los números son lo que separa un perfil bueno de uno excelente.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SIDE PROJECTS -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">4. Projects / Side Roles</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Añadir en la sección "Projects" de LinkedIn, o como roles separados en Experience. Esto es tu arma secreta (Walker: no-replicabilidad).</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-2">CHOWDOWN.ME — Founder</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-5 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">AI-powered food tracking app. Built from scratch, organically grown to 500+ monthly users.

Full product lifecycle: concept, design, development (TypeScript, Firebase, AI/LLM integration), content marketing, and SEO. Published 15+ blog posts driving organic traffic. Free forever model with affiliate and newsletter monetisation.

chowdown.me</div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-2">DARWIN.PAGE — Founder</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-5 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">AI landing page optimisation tool. Autonomously generates and tests page mutations to improve conversion rates.

Built the full stack: AI brain (TypeScript), SDK, portal (Next.js). Differentiator: AI generates mutations autonomously rather than requiring manual input.

darwin.page</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FEATURED -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">5. Featured Section</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">3 items que demuestren alto índice de ensamblaje. Portfolio visual de tu combinación única.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-lg">1</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-gray-200 font-semibold">chowdown.me</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Tu side project de AI con tracción real. Demuestra que construyes, no solo gestionas.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-lg">2</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-gray-200 font-semibold">darwin.page</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">AI product más técnico. Muestra profundidad en AI/ML aplicado a conversión.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-lg">3</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-gray-200 font-semibold">Tu primer post de LinkedIn (por escribir)</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Algo tipo "What I learned from Law that I use every day as a PM" o "I built an AI food tracker: here's what happened". Un post que solo tú puedes escribir.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ADVERSARIAL AUDIT -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">6. Adversarial Audit — Limpieza</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">De la #215: "Si alguien quisiera malinterpretar tu perfil, ¿qué vería?" Haz esto hoy.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-yellow-400 font-semibold">🔍 Skills: limpia el ruido</p>
            <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Revisa las 24 skills. Elimina todo lo genérico (Microsoft Office, etc.) que diluye tu señal. Reordena para que las top 3 sean: Product Strategy, AI/ML, Marketplace/Platform. Pide endorsements a colegas en esas tres.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-yellow-400 font-semibold">🔍 Idiomas: corregir</p>
            <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Spanish debería estar como "Native or bilingual proficiency" (primero). English "Native or bilingual". French "Professional working". Trilingüe es un diferenciador enorme para roles UK/EMEA.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-yellow-400 font-semibold">🔍 Educación: doble grado completo</p>
            <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Asegúrate de que aparece Law + Economics (o lo que sea exactamente). El combo jurídico-económico es fuerte para roles senior. Si "Marketing/Advertising" es un minor o similar, que quede claro.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-yellow-400 font-semibold">🔍 Title en Hire Space</p>
            <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Comprueba que dice "Head of Product", no "Senior Product Manager". Algunas fuentes externas (RocketReach, ContactOut) te listan como Senior PM todavía.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-yellow-400 font-semibold">🔍 "Open to Work"</p>
            <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm">Actívalo en modo "solo recruiters" si no lo tienes ya. No poner el marco verde público (señala desesperación), pero el flag privado sí multiplica las apariciones en búsquedas.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FIRST POST -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">7. Primer Post — Borrador</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">El de mayor impacto para tu narrativa: la historia de reinvención. Solo tú puedes escribir esto.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-3">BORRADOR — adapta con tu voz</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-5 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">I studied Law and Economics. Now I build AI products.

Not the most obvious career path. But here's what I've learned: the skills transfer more than you'd think.

Law taught me to read systems. To find the edge cases everyone else misses. To argue both sides before picking one.

Economics taught me to think in incentives. Why people do what they do. What happens when you change the rules.

Product management is where both come together.

For the last 5+ years, I've been Head of Product at Hire Space, building the UK's largest venue marketplace. 100K+ venues. Enterprise clients. The full spectrum of marketplace challenges: supply, demand, trust, pricing, scale.

On the side, I've been building with AI. An AI food tracker (chowdown.me). An AI landing page optimiser (darwin.page). Not because it's trendy, but because I wanted to understand the technology from the inside, not just manage a backlog about it.

The best product leaders I know have non-linear paths. The detours aren't bugs. They're features.

What's the most unexpected skill from a past life that you use daily?

#ProductManagement #AI #CareerChange</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-3">~1,000 caracteres. Formato LinkedIn: frases cortas, espaciado, hook al principio, pregunta al final para engagement. Adáptalo a tu voz.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RECOMMENDATIONS -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-blue-400">8. Recomendaciones — A quién pedir</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Tienes 2-3 buenas. Necesitas 4-6 diversas. Template para pedir:</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">PEDIR A:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Un engineering lead</strong> de Hire Space → valida que eres técnicamente creíble</li>
          <li><strong>Un stakeholder senior</strong> (CEO/CTO) → valida impacto estratégico</li>
          <li><strong>Un report directo</strong> (si gestionas equipo) → valida liderazgo</li>
          <li><strong>Un cliente o partner</strong> → valida impacto externo</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-green-400 font-semibold mb-2">TEMPLATE para pedir (adapta)</p>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 text-gray-200 text-sm leading-relaxed select-all" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Hey [name], I'm updating my LinkedIn and wondered if you'd be open to writing a short recommendation? 

Ideally something about [specific thing: how we worked together on X, the impact of Y, how I approach Z]. No pressure to make it long, a few sentences is perfect.

Happy to reciprocate if you'd like one too.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TIMELINE -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">📅 Timeline</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-bold whitespace-nowrap">HOY</span>
            <p class="text-gray-300">Headline + About + Open to Work (recruiters only). 15 minutos.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-yellow-400 font-bold whitespace-nowrap">MAÑANA</span>
            <p class="text-gray-300">Experiencia Hire Space (ambos roles). Limpieza de skills. Idiomas. 30 min.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-yellow-400 font-bold whitespace-nowrap">VIERNES</span>
            <p class="text-gray-300">Side projects (Chowdown + Darwin). Featured section. Pedir 3 recomendaciones. 20 min.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-400 font-bold whitespace-nowrap">LUNES</span>
            <p class="text-gray-300">Publicar primer post. Comentar en 5 posts de otros.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-green-400 font-bold whitespace-nowrap">SEM 2-4</span>
            <p class="text-gray-300">1 post/semana. 3-5 comentarios/día. Medir analytics (objetivo: 100+ views, 50+ search appearances).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="bg-gray-700/30 border border-gray-600/50 rounded-lg p-5 mb-10">
      <p class="text-gray-300">💡 Todo el texto de esta página es seleccionable. Haz click en cualquier bloque gris oscuro y copia directamente. Si quieres que ajuste algo (tono, contenido, enfoque), dime.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">Prepared by Rook 🏰 · Private & Confidential</p>
  </main>
</Layout>
